# Phase 4: Chat Experience and Stability Improvements

This phase transforms the functional chat core into a highly responsive, production-ready messaging experience by introducing typing indicators, read receipts, Glide image loading, robust lifecycle management, and Firestore security rules.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - I will be adding the `Glide` library to `build.gradle.kts` to handle asynchronous profile image loading and caching.
> - For tracking `onlineStatus` and `lastSeen`, I will update these fields in the `users` document directly from the `onResume` and `onPause` lifecycle methods of `MainActivity`.
> - Please review the proposed security rules and chat enhancements below.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Dependencies & App Lifecycle
#### [MODIFY] `build.gradle.kts`
- Add the `com.github.bumptech.glide:glide` dependency for robust image loading.

#### [MODIFY] `MainActivity.java`
- Override `onResume()` and `onPause()` to update the current user's `onlineStatus` ("online" / "offline") and `lastSeen` timestamp in Firestore.

### 2. Chat Experience Enhancements
#### [MODIFY] `ChatModel.java`
- Add `Map<String, Boolean> typing` to track typing status per participant.
- Add `Map<String, Integer> unreadCounts` for tracking unread messages per user.

#### [MODIFY] `MessageModel.java`
- Update the `isRead` boolean to a robust `status` string ("sent", "delivered", "read").

#### [MODIFY] `ChatActivity.java` & `ChatsFragment.java`
- **Typing Indicator**: Attach a `TextWatcher` to the message `EditText` to toggle the user's typing boolean in the `chats` document. Display "Typing..." in the Toolbar when the other participant's flag is true.
- **Status Observer**: Display "Online" or the formatted `lastSeen` time in the Toolbar subtitle.
- **Sorting**: Ensure `ChatsFragment` queries order by `lastMessageTimestamp DESCENDING`.
- **Auto-scroll**: Programmatically scroll to the bottom of the message `RecyclerView` on new snapshot data.

### 3. UI/UX Improvements
#### [NEW] `TimeUtils.java`
- A utility class for generating human-readable timestamps (e.g., "Today at 2:30 PM", "Yesterday", "Monday").

#### [MODIFY] Adapters (`UsersAdapter`, `PendingRequestsAdapter`, `ChatsAdapter`, `MessageAdapter`)
- Integrate Glide for all `iv_profile_image` views with a default placeholder if the image URL is empty.
- Utilize `TimeUtils` for formatted timestamps.

#### [MODIFY] All Fragments (`ChatsFragment`, `UsersFragment`, etc.)
- Enforce strict `ListenerRegistration` cleanup in `onDestroyView()` to prevent memory leaks and zombie listeners.

### 4. Firestore Security & Documentation
#### [NEW] `firestore.rules`
- Generate scalable security rules.
- Restrict read/write operations on the `chats` collection to users who exist within the `participants` map.
- Validate `chat_requests` to ensure `senderId == request.auth.uid`.

#### [NEW] `docs/` artifacts
- We will generate structured documentation, a testing checklist, and scalability recommendations.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Build and assemble the application (`./gradlew assembleDebug`) to ensure no dependency or syntax conflicts.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the app on two devices and verify the "Online" / "Last seen" status actively toggles in the Chat Toolbar.
2. Begin typing a message on Device A and verify "Typing..." immediately appears on Device B.
3. Validate that profile images are loaded smoothly using Glide.
4. Verify the Chats list dynamically sorts the most recently active chats to the top.
